##Junit 
What is Junit ??
Definition

JUnit is a Java Testing Framework used to automatically test Java applications.

Instead of checking outputs manually,

JUnit checks them automatically.

It tells you

✅ Passed

❌ Failed

## Why do we need JUnit?

<--Without JUnit-->

Run project
Call methods
Check output
Modify code
Run again
Repeat

..Very time consuming.

<--With JUnit-->

Run Tests
JUnit automatically checks
Pass/Fail
## What is Unit Testing ??
-> Testing each individual method is called Unit Testing.
For example 
in calculator class we run test cases for each method like add(), subtract(),multiply(),divide() .
